AHRQ specifically highlights equity and bias measurement as part of ED triage AI development.

8. Add per-patient explanation, not just global feature importance

Your XAI tab is good, but commercial-grade explainability needs patient-specific reasons.

Example:

Why ESI-2?

Chest pain with high-risk features
Systolic BP 185
Age 72
Likely requires multiple ED resources
Not safe for fast track

That is much stronger than a generic feature importance chart.

9. Add deterioration monitoring

Make the app re-check the waiting room every simulated 5 minutes.

Example:

Patient P004 has waited 38 minutes. HR increased from 112 to 128. SpO₂ dropped from 95% to 91%. Recommend re-triage and escalation.

That would look extremely badass because it moves from static triage to real-time ED surveillance.